From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Fri, 27 Feb 2026 19:06:43 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] drm/trilin-dptx: reset active_stream_cnt on HPD disconnect

When the DP cable is unplugged, trilin_dp_handle_disconnect() tears
down the PHY via core_off but does not reset active_stream_cnt.  On
replug, trilin_dp_ctrl_stream_on() increments the stale count (1->2),
causing the DP TX to misconfigure for dual-stream MST when only a
single SST stream is active.  The result is a black screen despite
successful link training and an enabled CRTC with a valid framebuffer.

Reset active_stream_cnt to 0 alongside the existing core_off and
state flag cleanup.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
index f03762da0defe..2eba2a509d4c2 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
@@ -2619,6 +2619,7 @@ int trilin_dp_handle_disconnect(struct trilin_dp *dp, bool send_notification)
 	 */
 	trilin_dp_core_off(dp);
 	dp->state &= ~DP_STATE_ENABLED;
+	dp->active_stream_cnt = 0;
 
 	if (dp->mst.mst_active) {
 		/* user mode should active power off to disable encoder */
